    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) represents the zenith of naturally aspirated performance. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a linear 333 hp up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory variable M differential lock. This specimen is mechanically impeccable: the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced, and rod bearing services are fully documented. The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing original-spec bushings and dampers to preserve the iconic telepathic steering feedback. Finished in showroom-quality Carbon Black over Cinnamon Nappa leather, this is an investment-grade example with no deferred maintenance and a pristine undercarriage.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Garage kept. No accidents. Full service history. New tires. Factory paint.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "Presenting a truly exceptional example of automotive preservation. This vehicle remains in absolute showroom condition, having been meticulously stored in a climate-controlled environment since day one. The exterior finish is flawless, treated with a multi-stage ceramic coating that highlights the deep, mirror-like luster of the original paint\u2014completely free of chips, swirls, or imperfections. Inside, the cabin still carries that distinct new-car scent; the premium leather upholstery is supple and shows zero signs of wear, while every electronic component and driver-assist feature functions exactly as it did the day it left the factory. Mechanically, this car is beyond reproach, with a comprehensive service history documented exclusively through authorized dealerships. It has never seen rain, let alone winter conditions. For the discerning collector or enthusiast who demands nothing less than perfection, this is the one.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
